The paper proposes a framework for localization and classification of masses in breast ultrasound images using deep learning. This falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of weakly and semi-supervised learning, which can be categorized under multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper presents experimental results and ablative analysis, which can be categorized under information retrieval (cs.IR).
